<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771051>
    dc:description "FIGURE 34. Mandible, inferior tooth. Scale=0.5 mm. A) Triangular, tip clearly angled (A. albata female, BBSL510289). B) Ovular, tip and general form rounded (A. estebana male, BBSL276281). C) Ridge-like, concave above, often projecting off main blade at tip (A. abroniae female, BBSL502235). D) Absent (A. abroniae male, BBSL502217)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3771051/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3771061>
